This is a class which creates a synchronized (thread-safe) key-value store backed by a tokyo cabinet Hash Database (HDB).

open

public void open(java.lang.String filePathAndName)
Open the database stored at the filePathName indicated. If the file doesn't exist it will be created. The file will be write locked while open by the file system. If the file is not closed the underlying database will be damaged.

Specified by:
open in class DB_LUCI
Parameters:
filePathAndName - The name of the file to open, e.g."eraseme.tch"
